:?
@X03Please type one of the indicated topics for additional help.
Press @X09<@X0CENTER@X09>@X03 alone to exit the help system.
~~
:+
:-
@X09(@X0C+@X09)@X03     Advance to next higher conference number.
@X09(@X0C-@X09)@X03     Go back to next lower conference number.
~~
:#
        You may specify any conference number.
        Full conference names can also be used to select conferences.
~~
:A
@X09(@X0CA@X09)@X03uto-join configuration update
~~
:L
@X09(@X0CL@X09)@X03ocate conference by keywords
~~
:M
@X09(@X0CM@X09)@X03ain board
~~
:N
@X09(@X0CN@X09)@X03ew message status
~~
:S
@X09(@X0CS@X09)@X03tatus of all conferences
~~
:Y
@X09(@X0CY@X09)@X03our mail.  Scan for conferences with new mail for you
~~
:EXAMPLES
@X0EJoin command examples:@X03

   J M         ;main board
   J;+         ;join next available conference
   J;6         ;join conference 6
   J TOOLS     ;join tools conference
   J L LANG    ;locate conferences with 'LANG' in the description
   J;2;Q       ;quick join, bypassing conference news
   J S         ;status of all conferences
   J S +       ;status of conferences after current one
   J A 20      ;configure autoscan starting with conference 20

~~
:SUMMARY
@X03The Join command allows you to switch to a different conference.  You
may specify either a conference number or a conference name.

These subfunctions are available:
   @X09(@X0CA@X09)@X03uto-join configuration update
   @X09(@X0CL@X09)@X03ocate conference by keywords
   @X09(@X0CM@X09)@X03ain board
   @X09(@X0CN@X09)@X03ew message status
   @X09(@X0CS@X09)@X03tatus of all conferences
   @X09(@X0CY@X09)@X03our mail.  Scan for conferences with new mail for you
   @X09(@X0C+@X09)@X03next higher conference
   @X09(@X0C-@X09)@X03next lower conference
~~

